              "cover_url": "https://p3-sign.douyinpic.com/tos-cn-i-0813c001/o4nsvebvAkceJeAB1lIEApEyDbQB1IwA7bFAnc~tplv-dy-resize-walign:360:q75.jpeg?lk3s=138a59ce&x-expires=1774756800&x-signature=wrN2SPWtgw%2FWwJIdgCPtJiU8UFA%3D&from=327834062&s=PackSourceEnum_PUBLISH&se=false&sc=cover&biz_tag=aweme_video&l=2026031512374679DF9F41DFBEC7DE9870",
              "script": "\"Do\"和\"make\"都表示做。那为什么做作业是\"do your homework\"，而做晚饭是\"make dinner\"？\n\n很简单，记住这条规则：如果从无到有，无中生有，我们就用\"make\"。比如说晚餐在做之前没有，所以是\"make dinner\"。同样的，做蛋糕\"make a cake\"，发出声音\"make a sound\"，交朋友\"make friends\"。\n\n如果之前本来就有，我们锦上添花就用\"do\"。作业本来就有，所以是\"do your homework\"。同样的，做家务\"do the housework\"，做头发\"do my hair\"，做指甲\"do my nails\"。\n\n你都学会了吗？学会了，给老师一颗小星星吧。"
