              "script": "The legend of Chinese New Year. A long, long time ago, in a small village in China, there was a big, scary, nasty beast named Nian. He had razor sharp teeth, giant claws and a really loud growl. On the darkest night of the year, when the new moon was in the sky, he would sneak into the village and scare everyone aside, even the animals, until a wise man taught them the three things Nian was afraid of: loud noises, fire, and the color red. The next time Nian came, the villagers fought back. They hit their drums as loud as they could, let off every firecracker they had, and they wore red from head to toe. Nian ran far away and never came back. After that, the celebration became a 15-day festival of family, food and good fortune called Chinese New Year. This is the legend of Chinese New Year. Did you learn it? If you did, give the teacher a star."
