              "script": "大家好，我是雪玲老师，又到了我们绘本的时间。今天我们来读的是和春节有关的绘本《Chinese New Year》，那我们一起来读吧。Let's read. Look, this is Maisie. Hello, Maisie, tomorrow is Chinese New Year. Maisie sweeps and tidies the house to get it ready. Hmm, Maisie, why do we clean the house before Chinese New Year? Because we need to sweep away the bad luck and make room for good luck in the New Year. Okay, now let's sweep, sweep, sweep, sweep.\n\nThen Maisie visits a market to buy food, decorations, and lovely new clothes. Look, this is the market. What can we see here? Flowers, plants, tangerines, and so many red clothes. Red is a lucky color. So what red things can you see? Yes, these lanterns are red, the clothes are red, the koala's hat is red. Oh, and the peacock is wearing a red scarf. Okay, now let's go home.\n\nAt home, Maisie waits for her first guest. Who's that knocking at the door? Oh, it's Tiger. She has come home to celebrate. Welcome Tiger. And who's next? Oh, Tallula, Charlie and Cyril, they arrive next. Hi everyone. Welcome Tiger. They all say hello. Happy New Year. Tiger has brought lots of presents and decorations to wish everyone happiness and luck. Look, they are hanging up the lanterns and the fu characters now. The house looks beautiful.\n\nOh, it's time for reunion dinner. They all sit at the table to eat a delicious feast. Mm, there's so many things to try. I can see fish, I can see noodles, I can see dumplings. Do you want to try them? Yum yum, says Charlie.\n\nAfter dinner, Ostrich and Penguin come to visit. They give everyone lucky red packets with money inside. It's lucky money. Thank you, says Maisie. Oh Maisie remember, you can say“恭喜发财”。\n\nBang. What's that sound? Oh, it's Tiger. The tiger hits the gong. It's story time. Maisie and her friends sit to listen to Tiger telling an exciting Chinese New Year's story. “A long, long time ago, twelve animals raced across a great river,” she begins. “The rat won the race, but we celebrate every animal in turn. This makes up the twelve-year Chinese zodiac,” Tiger explains. So do you know them? They are rat, ox, tiger, rabbit, Chinese dragon, which is long, snake, horse, goat, monkey, rooster, dog, pig. So what's your Chinese zodiac? I am a rooster.\n\nAt midnight, fireworks light up the sky to welcome the New Year. Boom, boom. Wow. So pretty. Some are round, some go out like stars, and everyone is happy. Okay?\n\nThe next day, everyone goes to a wonderful parade. They are dancing and singing. It's so much fun. Finally, Maisie leads friends in a special dragon dance for good luck. Happy New Year, Maisie. Happy New Year, everyone.\n\n好的，我们今天的故事就到这儿啦。想和雪玲老师一起来听更多的英文绘本，记得点赞收藏。And I will see you next time, bye."
