              "script": "和雪梨老师一起用英文讲好中国故事。\n\n端午节Dragon Boat Festival，also called端午节in Chinese，along with Chinese New year, tomb sweeping day and mid autumn festival, is one of the four most important traditional festivals for Chinese people. Although there are many legends about Dragon Boat Festival, it is today celebrated by most Chinese in memory of Qu Yuan, a minister in state. He was loved by the people at that time, but one day he became sad because his country was facing troubles. On the fifth day of the fifth lunar month, he jumped into the river because he knew he could no longer save it. Locals rushed into their boats to search for him. They threw rice balls, eggs and other food to keep fish from eating Qu Yuan's body. Fearing that the rice balls would be eaten by turtles, people wrapped rice with reed leaves and tied the leaves with colored silk thread. Thus zongzi appeared later to remember this great poet.\n\nCustoms like holding dragon boat races and eating zongzi at home were passed down. Different from other festivals, people never say happy Dragon Boat Festival, but say Duan Wu Ankang in Chinese when they greet each other. In 2009, the Dragon Boat Festival became China's first festival to be selected for the world's intangible cultural heritage.\n\n这就是端午节的由来，你都学会了吗？想跟雪梨老师一起来读更多中国故事，欢迎你每天早上八点来我的直播间，和我一起高效学习。"
